Date:  2/6/1915
Source:  Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page:  3
Edition:
Quote:  The new-born battalions, popularly known as "The Trents," were drawn up on the parade ground 2200 strong in the form of a hollow square, and presented a brave showing, the whole of the men, with the exception of a very small percentage, being well matured and of excellent physique.
